In a #small pot{}, combine @White Rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups @water{}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until Step 5.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Drain and rinse @Corn{1}(drained and rinsed), then pat very dry with #paper towels{}. Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add corn, @Fajita Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of salt and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until corn is golden brown and lightly charred in spots, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Cover with a lid if kernels start to pop!

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wipe out pan. Meanwhile, @Tomato{1}(diced into ½-inch pieces). @Scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Quarter @Lemon{1}.

Rinse @Shrimp{10%oz} under cold water; pat dry with paper towels. Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for corn over medium-high heat. Add shrimp in a single layer and season with @Mexican Spice Blend{1%tbsp} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are opaque and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

To bowl with charred corn, add tomato, half the scallions, a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tsp}, juice from one lemon wedge, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Stir to combine.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{3%tbsp}, juice from one lemon wedge, salt, and pepper to taste. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Stir in @Pepitas{1/2%oz}.

> TIP: If you have extra time, toast pepitas beforehand in a small dry skillet over medium
> heat, stirring frequently, for 1-2 minutes to add extra flavor and crunch!

Divide pepita rice between shallow #bowls{}. Using a #slotted spoon{}, top with salsa (draining first) and shrimp in separate sections. Drizzle with lemon crema and @Hot Sauce{1%tsp} as much as you like. Top with remaining scallions and serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.